SECTION: PREREQUISITES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIRED:
    - Java 21
    - Maven
    - Docker Desktop

VERIFY INSTALLATION:
    java -version
    mvn -version
    docker --version


SECTION: PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
demo/
│
├── src/
├── target/
├── pom.xml
└── Dockerfile


SECTION: STEP 1 - RUN APPLICATION LOCALLY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMAND:
    mvn spring-boot:run

ACCESS:
    http://localhost:8080

STOP:
    CTRL + C


SECTION: STEP 2 - BUILD JAR FILE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMAND:
    mvn clean package

OUTPUT:
    target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar

TEST JAR:
    java -jar target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


SECTION: STEP 3 - CREATE DOCKERFILE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FILENAME:
    Dockerfile

CONTENT:

    FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jdk-jammy
    WORKDIR /app
    COPY target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar app.jar
    EXPOSE 8080
    ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]


SECTION: STEP 4 - BUILD DOCKER IMAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMAND:
    docker build -t demo-app .

VERIFY:
    docker images


SECTION: STEP 5 - RUN DOCKER CONTAINER
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RUN (FOREGROUND):
    docker run -p 8080:8080 demo-app

RUN (DETACHED):
    docker run -d -p 8080:8080 demo-app

CHECK RUNNING CONTAINERS:
    docker ps

STOP CONTAINER:
    docker stop <container_id>

ACCESS:
    http://localhost:8080


SECTION: STEP 6 - PUSH IMAGE TO DOCKER HUB
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LOGIN:
    docker login

TAG IMAGE:
    docker tag demo-app yourusername/demo-app:1.0

PUSH IMAGE:
    docker push yourusername/demo-app:1.0

VERIFY:
    Check repository on Docker Hub


SECTION: STEP 7 - RUN ON ANOTHER MACHINE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LOGIN:
    docker login

PULL IMAGE:
    docker pull yourusername/demo-app:1.0

RUN:
    docker run -p 8080:8080 yourusername/demo-app:1.0

ACCESS:
    http://localhost:8080


================================================================================
WORKFLOW SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. DEVELOP      -> Spring Boot Application
2. BUILD        -> mvn clean package
3. CONTAINERIZE -> docker build
4. RUN          -> docker run
5. DISTRIBUTE   -> docker push
6. DEPLOY       -> docker pull + docker run
================================================================================
